history.content: Hi Folks I realized I left something out of the directions for the plots for Task 3 - you should plot the experimental results you find, the theoretically derived optimal k value and its false positive rate, and the theoretical values for false positive rate across all k values. The equation for this is in the notes for the bloom filter lecture. The point here is that your plots should show the performance of your bloom filter matching fairly closely the results predicted by theory. Sorry for the confusion
